column5: Morn,n Lew  Lew time is easy, once you get use to it.
Heck Brian this is Lew sleep in time. I can only imagine that him and Marv have been out in the forest talking to the deer and rabbits for a few hours now
Morning Gang. I enjoy getting up early.
yup...just leaving for work....if it friday yet.....
Mornin boyz, spring is in the air and I've been putzing around the house since 2:00.  It's a bit early for the deer yet Mike but perhaps it's time I went and got them up
Work has institutionalized me into waking up this early, even on the weekends when I do not have to.  December 30th 2041.  I retire.  It falls on a monday.  Aloha.
I'm on modified Lew time. My alarm is set for 4:50 every morning when I'm on day shift...and most mornings I'm up before it goes off.
That'll be 41 years and 3 months after MY retirement.  Jeeeez, I suddenly feel VERY old
I retire on a Thursday in 2049

Retire ???? Not sure if that ever truly happens to those of us who write our own paychecks ... slow down a bit or try take more time out for yourself ... heh ... been trying to do that all my life .. but retire ... I dunno ... do you HAVE to ?
You maybe getting use to Lew time, but i bet the deer are getting pissed off by him waking them up every morning!
As we speak Dan, there's 3 deer walking down the road towards the lake and none appear to be pi$$ed off
What, no video or pictures? They just tolerate it cause they know they are safe when they are around you!!
They know thier safe now. Did they stick their tonge out at ya Lew? LOL
Mornin guys and gals. God i hate gettin up early in the winter
